    public class CallBasicNode
extends CallNode
    Node representing a call to a basic template.

    Important: Do not use outside of Soy code (treat as superpackage-private).

      • CallBasicNode

        public CallBasicNode(int id,
                     String calleeName,
                     String srcCalleeName,
                     boolean useAttrStyleForCalleeName,
                     boolean useV1FunctionAttrForCalleeName,
                     boolean isPassingData,
                     boolean isPassingAllData,
                     @Nullable
                     ExprRootNode<?> dataExpr,
                     @Nullable
                     String userSuppliedPlaceholderName,
                     @Nullable
                     SyntaxVersionBound syntaxVersionBound,
                     com.google.common.collect.ImmutableList<String> escapingDirectiveNames)
        Parameters:
        id - The id for this node.
        calleeName - The full name of the template to call (including namespace).
        srcCalleeName - The callee name string as it appears in the source code.
        useAttrStyleForCalleeName - Whether to use name="..." when building command text.
        useV1FunctionAttrForCalleeName - Whether to use function="..." when building command text.
        isPassingData - True if the call forwards the data from dataRefText to its target.
        isPassingAllData - True if the call forwards all data from the template that contains it to its target.
        dataExpr - The expression for the data to pass, or null if not applicable.
        userSuppliedPlaceholderName - The user-supplied placeholder name, or null if not supplied or not applicable.
        syntaxVersionBound - The lowest known upper bound (exclusive!) for the syntax version of this node.
        escapingDirectiveNames - Call-site escaping directives used by strict autoescaping.
